# Foundation

## Stack
- Next.js (App Router)
- TypeScript only; never use JavaScript
- Tailwind CSS for all styling; no inline styles or CSS modules unless explicitly requested
- shadcn/ui before custom UI components
- Neon Postgres when needed
- Vercel for deployment

## Code Rules
- Always use TypeScript
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Prefer shadcn/ui components before building custom ones
- Keep components small and composable
- Use server components by default; use client components only when needed
- Write clean, lightweight code with no unnecessary dependencies
- Put all API routes in `src/app/api/`

## Folder Structure
- `src/components/ui` — shadcn/ui components
- `src/components/layout` — layout components such as header, footer, sidebar
- `src/components/shared` — reusable components across pages
- `src/lib` — utilities, helpers, API clients
- `src/hooks` — custom React hooks
- `src/types` — TypeScript type definitions
- `src/styles` — design tokens and global styles

## Design System
- Use design tokens from `src/styles/design-tokens.ts`
- Extend Tailwind config from those tokens when applicable
- Maintain consistent spacing, colors, and typography across components

## Cursor Workflow
- Use Composer/Agent for changes that touch more than one file
- After completing a task, always suggest the next logical step
- When adding a new component, check `src/components/ui` first before creating a new one
- When unsure about a pattern, prefer the simpler and more readable option
- Always show the full file path when referencing a file
- If a change affects types, update `src/types/` in the same edit

## Self-Improvement
- At the start of each session, review `.learnings/` files for relevant context
- After solving non-obvious issues or when corrected, log the learning to `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`
- Log errors and failed commands to `.learnings/ERRORS.md`
- Before major tasks, review recent learnings to avoid repeating past mistakes